00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,400
D A times D I.

587
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:09,770
You get to pick one

588
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:10,960
from A and one from I,

589
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:11,900
like in the Chinese restaurant,

590
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:12,480
one from A

591
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:13,120
and one from I.

592
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:13,840
Okay.

593
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,760
And how many are there all together?

594
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,660
D A times D I.

595
00:20:17,660 --> 00:20:19,040
That's why it's called a product,

596
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:22,140
because the dimensionality is a product.

597
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:29,120
So this is D A times D I in dimensionality.

598
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:32,780
These are the basis states for the tensor product.

599
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:33,660
Okay.

600
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:35,940
They're labeled with two indices.

601
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:36,900
Now,

602
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,500
you think of them as an orthonormal basis.

603
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,120
Orthonormal in the following sense.

604
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,340
If you take two such vectors,

605
00:20:44,340 --> 00:20:46,260
A I and let's say B J.

606
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:46,840
Okay.

607
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,140
Where B is another one

608
00:20:51,140 --> 00:20:53,260
of the basis vectors of A,

609
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:56,180
and J is another one of these.

610
00:20:58,700 --> 00:21:00,480
What's the inner product between these?

611
00:21:00,580 --> 00:21:04,780
Let's take these to be normalized vectors.

612
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,680
What is the inner product between them?

613
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:10,140
And the rule for a tensor product

614
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:12,400
is the inner product between this and this.

615
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:12,740
Of course,

616
00:21:12,740 --> 00:21:15,010
we have to make a bra vector out

617
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:17,280
of it in order to take its inner product.

618
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:17,640
Okay.

619
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:19,510
But if we made a bra vector out of

620
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:21,360
this and took its inner product with this one,

621
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,180
the

622
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:26,360
rule is that the inner product is zero unless A

623
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:30,540
is equal to B and I is equal to J.

624
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:31,760
In other words,

625
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:32,440
unless they match.

626
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,040
Okay.

627
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:35,600
If they don't match,

628
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,960
these might be observably different.

629
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:40,240
For example,

630
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,360
if this B was the same as this A,

631
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,840
but I was not the same as J,

632
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,940
then one half

633
00:21:46,940 --> 00:21:51,810
of the system here would be observable differences

634
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:56,680
associated with observable differences in the subsystem I.

635
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,360
So in order for them to have an overlap,

636
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:05,120
B must equal A and J must equal I,

637
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:08,160
and then they're observably the same vector.

638
00:22:08,780 --> 00:22:09,500
Excuse me.

639
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:13,580
Are these arbitrary vectors A and J?

640
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:14,400
These are basis vectors.

641
00:22:14,620 --> 00:22:16,660
So they're part of an orthonormal basis.

642
00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:17,020
Yes,

643
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:19,100
you could pick any orthonormal basis for this

644
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:21,180
one and any orthonormal basis for this one.

645
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:21,950
But why I have a number

646
00:22:21,950 --> 00:22:22,600
of these things we're talking about here?

647
00:22:22,660 --> 00:22:22,740
Yeah.

648
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:23,340
Okay.

649
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:23,440
Yeah.

650
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,930
But you could pick any orthonormal basis from

651
00:22:25,930 --> 00:22:28,260
this one and any orthonormal basis from this

652
00:22:28,260 --> 00:22:29,680
one and put them together this

653
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,100
way and you'll get the same result.

654
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,220
It doesn't matter which basis you pick,

655
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:35,640
but let's pick a basis to be concrete.

656
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,220
Let's pick a basis.

657
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:40,050
If A and I are not

658
00:22:40,050 --> 00:22:41,420
the same as both B and J,

659
00:22:41,420 --> 00:22:43,020
the inner product is zero.

660
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,220
I can write an equation for that.

661
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:49,760
B,

662
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:50,140
J,

663
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:52,060
A,

664
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:54,520
I is equal to delta,

665
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,820
Kronecker delta,

666
00:22:55,820 --> 00:22:57,360
A,

667
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:57,640
B,

668
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:58,960
Kronecker delta,

669
00:22:58,960 --> 00:22:59,280
I,

670
00:22:59,280 --> 00:22:59,620
J.

671
00:23:00,940 --> 00:23:03,510
If I is not equal to J

672
00:23:03,510 --> 00:23:06,080
or A is not equal to B,

673
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:07,600
this is zero.

674
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:09,940
It's only non-zero if I is equal

675
00:23:09,940 --> 00:23:11,940
to J and A is equal to B.

676
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,360
So?

677
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:16,920
These vectors form a vector.

678
00:23:16,940 --> 00:23:17,400
Formally,

679
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,120
by construction,

680
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,540
by construction,

681
00:23:19,540 --> 00:23:21,580
which means you're simply assigning values

682
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:22,240
to things now,

683
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:25,600
but in a way that is useful,

684
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:29,480
these vectors form,

685
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,540
by definition or by construction,

686
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:35,140
an orthonormal basis for the combined system.

687
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,580
And this makes sense.

688
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:40,920
Excuse me,

689
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:41,460
another question?

690
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:41,940
Mm-hmm?

691
00:23:43,220 --> 00:23:46,340
And you've defined it's dependent upon the basis by...

692
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:46,700
It does.

693
00:23:46,940 --> 00:23:47,200
But actually,

694
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:48,860
as I defined it,

695
00:23:48,860 --> 00:23:49,780
let's put it this way.

696
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:51,440
The words depend on the basis.

697
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:54,020
The construction in the end doesn't.

698
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:55,660
The construction in the end doesn't,

699
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:56,860
and that's not hard to show.

700
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:57,780
This is,

701
00:23:57,780 --> 00:23:58,180
however,

702
00:23:58,180 --> 00:24:01,110
keep in mind that these basis vectors

703
00:24:01,110 --> 00:24:04,040
are not all of the vectors in

704
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:04,680
the tensor product.

705
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:06,970
You can then take any

706
00:24:06,970 --> 00:24:08,900
linear combination of these basis vectors,

707
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:12,120
and they're also a vector

708
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,360
in the tensor product.

709
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:14,160
So,

710
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:17,990
the general vector in the tensor product is

711
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:21,820
of the form sum over I and A,

712
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:23,860
alpha,

713
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:24,200
let's

714
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,920
call it some IA,

715
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:28,280
IA.

716
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:32,390
A general linear combination with coefficients

717
00:24:32,390 --> 00:24:35,040
that depend on what's inside here,

718
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,360
times the

719
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:36,640
vector,

720
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:37,920
times the basis vectors.

721
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:38,780
Now,

722
00:24:38,780 --> 00:24:39,580
the answer is,

723
00:24:39,580 --> 00:24:42,120
if you were to have chosen another basis.

724
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:43,620
Another vector.

725
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,160
Another set of bases.

726
00:24:44,540 --> 00:24:47,180
You would have gotten exactly the same vectors,

727
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:49,280
except they would have been written differently.

728
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,410
They would have just been written in

729
00:24:51,410 --> 00:24:53,220
a different basis of the combined system.

730
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:56,130
Changing basis for the individual systems corresponds

731
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:58,400
to a basis change for the combined

732
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:58,820
system.

733
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,100
Okay,

734
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,520
so that's good.

735
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:03,360
And we now have the idea of a tensor product.

736
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:06,160
And I'm going to give you a concrete example now.

737
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:08,810
The concrete example is the

738
00:25:08,810 --> 00:25:11,060
next most complicated quantum system.

739
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:13,340
Namely two spins.

740
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:14,980
Well,

741
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:16,760
it's debatable whether it's the next most

742
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:18,540
complicated or the next to next most

743
00:25:18,540 --> 00:25:19,100
complicated.

744
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:22,180
And the reason I say that is

745
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:24,920
because two spins have four basis vectors.

746
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:28,080
You could imagine a system with only three basis vectors,

747
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:29,600
and such systems exist.

748
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,380
But since we're trying to learn how to combine systems,

749
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:38,140
let's take two systems and combine

750
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:38,500
them,

751
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:41,600
each of them being a spin.

752
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:43,060
So what do we have?

753
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,420
We have an electron nailed

754
00:25:45,420 --> 00:25:47,200
down at this position over here,

755
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,660
and it has a spin,

756
00:25:48,660 --> 00:25:49,840
which we're

757
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:50,820
going to call sigma.

758
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:52,380
And it has three components,

759
00:25:52,380 --> 00:25:52,980
sigma,

760
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:53,360
x,

761
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:53,740
y,

762
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:54,120
and z.

763
00:25:55,179 --> 00:25:55,980
So sigma,

764
00:25:55,980 --> 00:25:56,220
x,

765
00:25:56,220 --> 00:25:56,460
y,

766
00:25:56,460 --> 00:25:56,780
and z.

767
00:26:02,259 --> 00:26:04,060
And we have another one over here.

768
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:06,500
We need a name for it.

769
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:07,970
Now I toyed for a while

770
00:26:07,970 --> 00:26:09,320
with calling this one sigma one,

771
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:10,360
this one sigma two,

772
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:10,800
but there

773
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:11,640
were too many indices.

774
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:13,620
Then I had sigma two.

775
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,060
Sigma one x,

776
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:14,800
sigma one y,

777
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:15,780
but they're bad.

778
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:18,140
So I decided to give this one another name.

779
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:21,400
And the Greek letter that comes after sigma is tau.

780
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,420
I don't know if it's the next letter.

781
00:26:23,660 --> 00:26:24,800
It's the one in the English alphabet,

782
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,100
st,

783
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:25,480
yeah.

784
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:26,640
So the next one I think

785
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:27,680
in the Greek alphabet is tau.

786
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:30,980
And I simply call this one tau.

787
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:33,940
How many components does tau have?

788
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:36,180
Well tau is also a spin.

789
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,520
So it also has three components,

790
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:38,800
x,

791
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:39,020
y,

792
00:26:39,020 --> 00:26:39,320
and z.

793
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,700
Supposing I choose for the

794
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:47,760
basis vectors for each of these,

795
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:50,260
the up and down basis vectors.

796
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:52,140
In other words,

797
00:26:52,140 --> 00:26:57,860
the states in which sigma z is up or down,

798
00:26:57,860 --> 00:27:00,200
and the states in which tau

799
00:27:00,399 --> 00:27:02,560
z are up and down.

800
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:12,120
Then our basis vectors for sigma are up and down.

801
00:27:12,180 --> 00:27:12,840
Okay.

802
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:17,840
Our basis vectors for tau are exactly the same.

803
00:27:20,660 --> 00:27:22,840
Up and down.

804
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:26,250
And maybe in order to indicate that

805
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:29,600
these are vectors for the system tau,

806
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:30,720
and these

807
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,200
are vectors for the system sigma,

808
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:35,480
let's use a slightly different kind of bracket notation

809
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:35,900
here.

810
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:38,220
Let's use a curly bracket.

811
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:41,220
I'm going to give that up very shortly.

812
00:27:41,420 --> 00:27:42,520
I just want to point out

813
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:43,620
to you that these are the two.

814
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:44,460
These are different than these.

815
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:45,980
And down.

816
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:50,960
So good.

817
00:27:51,460 --> 00:27:54,680
What is the basis vectors for the combined system?

818
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,300
If we put the systems together,

819
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:59,040
what are the basis vectors for the combined system?

820
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:00,540
There are four of them.

821
00:28:00,740 --> 00:28:01,660
Two times two is four.

822
00:28:02,380 --> 00:28:03,380
And what are they?

823
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:06,300
They are states in which both spins are up.

824
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:08,820
That's one of them.

825
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,400
One spin.

826
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:13,600
And I'll always take the first entry here to correlate.

827
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:13,930
The first entry is the

828
00:28:13,930 --> 00:28:14,260
first entry to correspond to sigma.

829
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,960
And the second entry to correspond to tau.

830
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,500
Up down.

831
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:22,800
Down up.

832
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:24,880
And down down.

833
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:29,220
That's the four basis vectors.

834
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:33,580
Each basis vector carrying two labels now.

835
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:37,280
A sigma label and a tau label.

836
00:28:38,940 --> 00:28:40,080
That's the idea.

837
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:42,180
And it's a very reasonable idea.

838
00:28:42,860 --> 00:28:43,580
I'm going to go back to the first one.

839
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:44,160
Yes.

840
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,740
Suppose these two component systems interact.

841
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:49,220
Doesn't that change things somehow?

842
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:49,780
No,

843
00:28:49,780 --> 00:28:51,320
the basis vectors stay the same.

844
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:53,650
But the linear combination of basis vectors

845
00:28:53,650 --> 00:28:55,840
that they're describing the system will change.

846
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:56,720
Yeah.

847
00:28:57,340 --> 00:29:02,850
So any state in this space can be written as

848
00:29:02,850 --> 00:29:08,360
an alpha up up times up up plus an alpha

849
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:10,740
up down up down.

850
00:29:11,540 --> 00:29:12,180
Plus.

851
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:13,580
An alpha down up down.

852
00:29:13,580 --> 00:29:22,760
Down up plus an alpha down down down down.

853
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:28,100
That's the most general thing we can write.

854
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:30,780
Let's call it psi.

855
00:29:31,100 --> 00:29:33,800
The answer to your question is if

856
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:36,500
you started out with a particular linear combination.

857
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:40,840
Let's say for example just alpha up up up up.

858
00:29:40,860 --> 00:29:41,520
Both spins up.

859
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:42,480
And you let them interact.

860
00:29:43,580 --> 00:29:44,980
Then in general what will

861
00:29:44,980 --> 00:29:46,380
happen is these coefficients will change.

862
00:29:46,820 --> 00:29:49,770
In fact it could even happen that after a

863
00:29:49,770 --> 00:29:52,720
time alpha up up might go to alpha down down.

864
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:57,240
In other words two spins up might interact in

865
00:29:57,240 --> 00:30:00,320
such a way as to just wind up down.

866
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,530
That would not be a change

867
00:30:02,530 --> 00:30:04,020
in what the basis vectors are.

868
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:06,860
It would be a change in what the alphas are.

869
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:07,940
Okay.

870
00:30:08,100 --> 00:30:08,620
So.

871
00:30:09,260 --> 00:30:09,780
Uh.

872
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:12,560
Okay.

873
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:13,560
So.

874
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:21,400
